# Persistent Project Context

- Before starting work, check `.agent-memory/PROJECT_CONTEXT.md`, `.agent-memory/SCHEMA_SUMMARY.md`, `.agent-memory/BRAND_CONTEXT.md`, `.agent-memory/MANUAL_NOTES.md`, `.agent-memory/ROADMAP.md`, `.agent-memory/WORKING_LOG.md`.
- Code is the source of truth; `.agent-memory/*.md` are fast-recovery cache contexts.
- Before UI/UX/branding work, always read `BRAND_CONTEXT.md` first.
- When user mentions roadmap, TODO, backlog, "remember this" — read `ROADMAP.md` first.
- Brand principles not in `BRAND_CONTEXT.md` must not be assumed.
- Before any feature work, read `FEATURE_MAP.md` to identify all affected portals/platforms.
- **Reference First**: Before implementing on any platform, check if the same feature already exists elsewhere. If so, read that code first and match fields, flows, validations, and API calls.
- **Completeness Check**: Never build only the happy path. Check auth flows, error/edge cases, real device environments, adjacent features, and server API coverage.
- **Cross-platform Check**: Before completing any change, verify whether it needs to be reflected on other platforms. Always check regardless of change type.
- After meaningful changes, add a brief record to `WORKING_LOG.md`.
- When modifying `.agent-memory/` docs, always tell the user explicitly what changed.
